2. Prohibited Uses

The Software, and any modified version, derivative work, service, product, or
system that incorporates, links to, depends on, or is materially enabled by the
Software, may not be used, directly or indirectly, for any of the following:

a. Weapons

Designing, developing, manufacturing, training, testing, simulating, targeting,
deploying, operating, maintaining, selling, or otherwise enabling weapons,
weapon systems, munitions, autonomous or semi-autonomous targeting systems,
or systems intended to cause physical injury, death, or destruction.

b. Surveillance

Creating, enabling, operating, supporting, or materially improving systems used
for surveillance, tracking, identification, profiling, monitoring, interception,
or analysis of individuals or groups without their informed consent.

This includes, without limitation, systems used for mass surveillance, biometric
identification, location tracking, communications monitoring, predictive policing,
social scoring, or targeted monitoring of activists, journalists, workers,
minorities, political opponents, or other vulnerable groups.

3. Ordinary Security and Operations Exception

The restriction on surveillance does not prohibit reasonable, disclosed, and
proportionate uses of the Software for ordinary software observability, debugging,
fraud prevention, access control, abuse prevention, system security, compliance
logging, or protection of users and systems, provided that such uses are not
designed or deployed for prohibited surveillance purposes.

4. No Circumvention

No person or entity may use the Software to assist, enable, or provide services
to another person or entity where the person or entity knows, or reasonably
should know, that the Software will be used for a prohibited purpose described
above.

5. Termination

Any rights granted under this License terminate automatically for any person or
entity that violates Section 2 or Section 4. Upon termination, that person or
entity must cease all use, copying, modification, distribution, sublicensing,
and sale of the Software and any modified version, derivative work, service,
product, or system that incorporates or is materially enabled by the Software.

